y of several farmsteads so named, from Old Norse <i>tupt</i> ‘site, lot’.","Possibly an altered form of South German <b>Duft</b>, a topographic name meaning ‘swamp, moor’."]},{"name":"Taft","meanings":["English (mainly Staffordshire and Derbyshire): variant of   Toft  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): artificial or metonymic occupational name from German <i>Taft</i> ‘taffeta’.","History: Robert Taft (born <i>c.</i> 1640), lived in Braintree, MA, and subsequently Mendon, MA. — Alphonso Taft (1810–91), jurist and politician born in Townshend, VT, was the father of William Howard Taft (1857–1930), 27th president of the US and chief justice of the US Supreme Court."]},{"name":"Tofte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Hjalmer, Iver, Steinar, Thora.","Scandinavian (mainly Norwegian): variant of   Toft  ."]}]},{"name":"Arnold","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  Jewish: Yiddish contracted form of   Aaron .","2  English: short form of   Arnold ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705183,"age":3,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":13,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":23,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"Ki